1558024.folder: Park Avenue - East 80th Street, Manhattan, NY
1558024.title: Park Avenue - East 80th Street

714597f-a.text:
121-125 East 80th Street, north side, between Park and Lexington Avenues.
About 1911.

714598f-a.text:
112 East 80th Street, south side, east of Park Avenue.
About 1911.

722345f-a.text:
911 Park Avenue, at S. E. corner of 80th Street, A new apartment building replaces the old 7-story Alvarado apartments.
About 1926.
Joseph Smith, Photographer.

722346f-a.text:
925 to 935 Park Ave., east side, from East 80th (right) to 81st (left) Streets, showing prominently a 12-story apartment house in the center of the block and bearing No. 929. The clearance seen, was caused by the demolition of two 5-story structures (Nos. 933 and 935) and upon which will rise a 12-story building. Partially shown on the right is a 14-story corner structure that was erected in 1907 and is said to be the first apartment building of over 6-stories on Park Ave. According to the New York Times of December 5, 1937 this structure has been completely modernized with the exclusion of 1 apartment, which has been occupied
by the same tenant for 30 years.
1922.
Collins.
Gift of E. M. Jenks.

722347f-a.text:
Park Avenue, south from 81st Street. Note new apartment building on the S.W. corner of 79th Street. The oldest buildings in the foreground are the ones on the N.W. corner of 80th Street, survivors of the pre-apartment house days.

1930.

Ewing Galloway, Photographer.
